00:58:34.540 --> 00:58:38.258 align:middle line:84%
we could have some
wine for dinner.

00:58:38.258 --> 00:58:42.650 align:middle line:90%


00:58:42.650 --> 00:58:44.130 align:middle line:90%
>> Don't you get bored?

00:58:44.130 --> 00:58:44.930 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:58:44.930 --> 00:58:45.090 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:58:45.090 --> 00:58:45.560 align:middle line:90%
Not at all.

00:58:45.560 --> 00:58:46.360 align:middle line:90%
Never.

00:58:46.360 --> 00:58:47.750 align:middle line:90%
>> So how do you not get bored?

00:58:47.750 --> 00:58:51.080 align:middle line:84%
>> My biggest hobby
is woodworking.

00:58:51.080 --> 00:58:54.280 align:middle line:84%
And I woodwork the old-fashioned
way-- with hand tools.

00:58:54.280 --> 00:59:04.190 align:middle line:90%


00:59:04.190 --> 00:59:08.510 align:middle line:84%
>> The wintertime,
it's more indoor stuff.

00:59:08.510 --> 00:59:11.940 align:middle line:84%
For me, it might be sewing,
quilting, knitting, spinning,

00:59:11.940 --> 00:59:12.740 align:middle line:90%
weaving.

00:59:12.740 --> 00:59:14.310 align:middle line:90%
I mean, any--

00:59:14.310 --> 00:59:16.228 align:middle line:90%
I love doing any that stuff.

00:59:16.228 --> 00:59:40.780 align:middle line:90%


00:59:40.780 --> 00:59:43.410 align:middle line:84%
>> The one next to the
vent, the higher one,

00:59:43.410 --> 00:59:47.340 align:middle line:90%
is the TV satellite.

00:59:47.340 --> 00:59:50.830 align:middle line:84%
And then the one that's
all close to the porch

00:59:50.830 --> 00:59:53.775 align:middle line:84%
is the internet
satellite system.

00:59:53.775 --> 00:59:56.150 align:middle line:84%
When we built the house, that
was one of the first things

00:59:56.150 --> 00:59:58.890 align:middle line:90%
that we put in was the TV.

00:59:58.890 --> 01:00:01.820 align:middle line:84%
>> I think we've
only met, one, two,

01:00:01.820 --> 01:00:08.040 align:middle line:84%
three people that didn't have
the internet in their home.

01:00:08.040 --> 01:00:09.740 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand,
we've only met

01:00:09.740 --> 01:00:14.180 align:middle line:84%
a handful of people that
have a TV, satellite,

01:00:14.180 --> 01:00:15.920 align:middle line:90%
or cable subscription.

01:00:15.920 --> 01:00:22.056 align:middle line:84%
I'm wondering why you decided to
have TV when you're so remote?

01:00:22.056 --> 01:00:24.080 align:middle line:90%
>> For the entertainment value.

01:00:24.080 --> 01:00:27.600 align:middle line:84%
We're not big on the
soaps and stuff like that.

01:00:27.600 --> 01:00:30.980 align:middle line:84%
Well, we don't
watch them at all.

01:00:30.980 --> 01:00:37.410 align:middle line:84%
But the educational TV is
something that we do enjoy.

01:00:37.410 --> 01:00:38.750 align:middle line:90%
So we watch a couple--

01:00:38.750 --> 01:00:39.680 align:middle line:90%
three hours a day.

01:00:39.680 --> 01:00:40.550 align:middle line:10%
I mean--

01:00:40.550 --> 01:00:42.620 align:middle line:10%
>> When you're alone in
this place in the middle

01:00:42.620 --> 01:00:46.460 align:middle line:10%
of the winter and it's minus 30
outside, you're going no place.

01:00:46.460 --> 01:00:49.110 align:middle line:10%
You're staying at home
watching TV, or you're reading.

01:00:49.110 --> 01:00:51.660 align:middle line:10%
I read a lot.

01:00:51.660 --> 01:00:56.600 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't watch TV unless it's
Saturday night and the hockey

01:00:56.600 --> 01:00:57.780 align:middle line:90%
game's on.

01:00:57.780 --> 01:01:01.682 align:middle line:84%
And at the same time,
I'm grinding flour

01:01:01.682 --> 01:01:03.800 align:middle line:90%
on an exercise bike.

01:01:03.800 --> 01:01:06.590 align:middle line:84%
So it's my compromise
with the devil.

01:01:06.590 --> 01:01:10.430 align:middle line:84%
I'm consuming our
energy, in a sense,

01:01:10.430 --> 01:01:13.310 align:middle line:90%
frivolously using the energy.

01:01:13.310 --> 01:01:15.380 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time,
I'm saying, well,

01:01:15.380 --> 01:01:17.450 align:middle line:84%
if I'm going to be
so darn frivolous,

01:01:17.450 --> 01:01:19.520 align:middle line:90%
then I better grind some grain.

01:01:19.520 --> 01:01:20.940 align:middle line:84%
Actually, that's
what Nan told me.

01:01:20.940 --> 01:01:21.830 align:middle line:90%
>> [CHUCKLE]

01:01:21.830 --> 01:01:24.080 align:middle line:10%
>> Quite honestly, there's
nothing on television worth

01:01:24.080 --> 01:01:25.063 align:middle line:10%
watching.

01:01:25.063 --> 01:01:26.980 align:middle line:10%
And I just got so that
I wasn't even using it.

01:01:26.980 --> 01:01:28.910 align:middle line:10%
And one day I stopped
and I thought, jeez,

01:01:28.910 --> 01:01:31.580 align:middle line:10%
that thing hasn't been
on for at least a year.

01:01:31.580 --> 01:01:34.730 align:middle line:84%
Why am I even
bothering to dust it?

01:01:34.730 --> 01:01:36.200 align:middle line:90%
And so I threw it out.

01:01:36.200 --> 01:01:39.740 align:middle line:10%
>> Television is always pushing.

01:01:39.740 --> 01:01:48.680 align:middle line:10%
I use the internet for emails
and for looking things up.

01:01:48.680 --> 01:01:51.200 align:middle line:90%


01:01:51.200 --> 01:01:57.060 align:middle line:84%
And I go there, and
if I want the news,

01:01:57.060 --> 01:02:01.550 align:middle line:84%
I'll go to Al Jazeera or
BBC or someplace like that--

01:02:01.550 --> 01:02:05.610 align:middle line:84%
not Fox News or
someplace like that--

01:02:05.610 --> 01:02:06.800 align:middle line:90%
and read the news.

01:02:06.800 --> 01:02:09.230 align:middle line:90%
And then they turn it off.

01:02:09.230 --> 01:02:13.800 align:middle line:84%
The computer is kind of like
a crescent wrench for me.

01:02:13.800 --> 01:02:14.600 align:middle line:90%
It's a tool.

01:02:14.600 --> 01:02:32.100 align:middle line:90%


01:02:32.100 --> 01:02:34.620 align:middle line:84%
>> I run the Lotus
Center in St. John's.

01:02:34.620 --> 01:02:36.580 align:middle line:84%
And that's a yoga and
meditation center,

01:02:36.580 --> 01:02:39.310 align:middle line:84%
and lots of
spiritual activities.

01:02:39.310 --> 01:02:40.730 align:middle line:10%
And when I met Ian--

01:02:40.730 --> 01:02:43.970 align:middle line:10%
I've been always looking
for a place to do a retreat.

01:02:43.970 --> 01:02:46.470 align:middle line:10%
And Ian has been--

01:02:46.470 --> 01:02:48.870 align:middle line:10%
he has this land out
here, and he's wondering

01:02:48.870 --> 01:02:50.860 align:middle line:10%
what he's going to do with it.

01:02:50.860 --> 01:02:57.540 align:middle line:10%
So the two of us got together
and brainstormed this vision.

01:02:57.540 --> 01:03:01.050 align:middle line:90%
We have the meditation hut.

01:03:01.050 --> 01:03:04.480 align:middle line:84%
And that has two
accommodations in there.

01:03:04.480 --> 01:03:08.170 align:middle line:10%
And we also have the new bunk
house that we're building.

01:03:08.170 --> 01:03:10.590 align:middle line:10%
So that will
accommodate 12 people.

01:03:10.590 --> 01:03:13.320 align:middle line:84%
So we'll have someone
coming for the day,

01:03:13.320 --> 01:03:15.820 align:middle line:90%
someone coming for the weekend.

01:03:15.820 --> 01:03:18.270 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes people stay
for a week or two.

01:03:18.270 --> 01:03:21.360 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we have
a work exchange

01:03:21.360 --> 01:03:23.430 align:middle line:84%
where people come out
and work, and they stay

01:03:23.430 --> 01:03:25.410 align:middle line:90%
for accommodation and food.

01:03:25.410 --> 01:03:28.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Miranda brought more of
the people aspect to it.

01:03:28.980 --> 01:03:33.310 align:middle line:84%
I'm bringing more the nature and
building since my training was

01:03:33.310 --> 01:03:34.110 align:middle line:90%
in science.

01:03:34.110 --> 01:03:38.700 align:middle line:90%


01:03:38.700 --> 01:03:40.750 align:middle line:84%
>> When I lived in India,
it was a lifestyle.

01:03:40.750 --> 01:03:42.150 align:middle line:90%
It was a spiritual lifestyle.

01:03:42.150 --> 01:03:44.970 align:middle line:90%
So it wasn't really a business.

01:03:44.970 --> 01:03:50.700 align:middle line:84%
When I came back to
the West, Canada,

01:03:50.700 --> 01:03:55.140 align:middle line:84%
it was like looking around and
saying everything's a business.

01:03:55.140 --> 01:03:58.020 align:middle line:84%
Everything's in terms
of making a living

01:03:58.020 --> 01:04:02.548 align:middle line:84%
and how to design it so that
$1 comes out at the end of it.

01:04:02.548 --> 01:04:03.840 align:middle line:10%
I had to get my head around it.

01:04:03.840 --> 01:04:06.490 align:middle line:10%
For several years, I had
to get my head around it.

01:04:06.490 --> 01:04:09.710 align:middle line:10%
But I came with a desire
to create community.

01:04:09.710 --> 01:04:14.640 align:middle line:84%
>> The freedom of waking up in
the morning and you don't have

01:04:14.640 --> 01:04:15.525 align:middle line:90%
to be somewhere else.

01:04:15.525 --> 01:04:17.868 align:middle line:90%


01:04:17.868 --> 01:04:19.410 align:middle line:84%
You've still got a
lot on your plate,

01:04:19.410 --> 01:04:21.990 align:middle line:84%
maybe, that you want to
touch down on that day.

01:04:21.990 --> 01:04:27.510 align:middle line:84%
But you're not going to company
B and putting in your day.

01:04:27.510 --> 01:04:30.240 align:middle line:84%
You're just waking up
and you can choose what

01:04:30.240 --> 01:04:31.920 align:middle line:90%
it is you're going to work on.

01:04:31.920 --> 01:04:33.600 align:middle line:84%
>> When we first did this, we
didn't really have to get a job

01:04:33.600 --> 01:04:36.260 align:middle line:84%
because we had money from
the sale of our other stuff.

01:04:36.260 --> 01:04:39.637 align:middle line:10%
But that quickly ran out
over a period of time.

01:04:39.637 --> 01:04:40.470 align:middle line:10%
We built everything.

01:04:40.470 --> 01:04:41.345 align:middle line:10%
We bought everything.

01:04:41.345 --> 01:04:43.830 align:middle line:10%
So we really didn't
have any bills.

01:04:43.830 --> 01:04:45.503 align:middle line:84%
But we got to the
point where we knew

01:04:45.503 --> 01:04:47.670 align:middle line:84%
we were going to have to
do something for an income.

01:04:47.670 --> 01:04:49.800 align:middle line:84%
And we always thought
the whole time, well,

01:04:49.800 --> 01:04:53.160 align:middle line:84%
when that comes, why don't we
see if we can't sell what we

01:04:53.160 --> 01:04:54.370 align:middle line:90%
love, which is our lifestyle.

01:04:54.370 --> 01:04:55.600 align:middle line:90%
You know what I mean?

01:04:55.600 --> 01:04:56.850 align:middle line:90%
So that's what it kind of did.

01:04:56.850 --> 01:04:59.910 align:middle line:84%
And she does-- you can see a
lot of the things that she does.

01:04:59.910 --> 01:05:00.780 align:middle line:90%
She has a website.

01:05:00.780 --> 01:05:02.880 align:middle line:84%
And she does shows
and she sells crafts

01:05:02.880 --> 01:05:05.220 align:middle line:90%
and art and stuff like that.

01:05:05.220 --> 01:05:08.070 align:middle line:10%
>> Friday I should be getting
my very first old-age pension

01:05:08.070 --> 01:05:09.090 align:middle line:10%
check.

01:05:09.090 --> 01:05:12.320 align:middle line:10%
So I don't know how much
they've cut my Canada pension--

01:05:12.320 --> 01:05:14.940 align:middle line:10%
Quebec pension, pardon me.

01:05:14.940 --> 01:05:16.410 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
I'm getting yet.

01:05:16.410 --> 01:05:18.150 align:middle line:84%
It might turn out to
be so little that I

01:05:18.150 --> 01:05:19.480 align:middle line:90%
can't afford to stay here.

01:05:19.480 --> 01:05:24.570 align:middle line:84%
>> Nan retired in 1976,
worked part-time on occasion.

01:05:24.570 --> 01:05:26.820 align:middle line:10%
Was always very
supportive of me when

01:05:26.820 --> 01:05:29.310 align:middle line:10%
I needed help, which was daily.

01:05:29.310 --> 01:05:31.525 align:middle line:10%
>> [CHUCKLE]

01:05:31.525 --> 01:05:33.420 align:middle line:90%
>> And the kids, the three kids.

01:05:33.420 --> 01:05:37.350 align:middle line:84%
Nan had time to pretty
well go full-time at this

01:05:37.350 --> 01:05:42.720 align:middle line:84%
as I tried to keep my
job and pitch in here.

01:05:42.720 --> 01:05:46.170 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think that a couple
who both work full-time could

01:05:46.170 --> 01:05:47.940 align:middle line:90%
live off-the-grid?

01:05:47.940 --> 01:05:48.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Off-the-grid, yes.

01:05:48.990 --> 01:05:50.520 align:middle line:90%
But not quite like we do.

01:05:50.520 --> 01:05:52.890 align:middle line:84%
>> But if you're going
to go the extra step,

01:05:52.890 --> 01:05:55.950 align:middle line:90%
then it takes a rare family.

01:05:55.950 --> 01:05:58.990 align:middle line:84%
You need two partners
who are raring to go.

01:05:58.990 --> 01:05:59.790 align:middle line:90%
That's the key.

01:05:59.790 --> 01:06:06.230 align:middle line:84%
You do need a second person
and a supportive family.

01:06:06.230 --> 01:06:09.270 align:middle line:10%
>> Do you think it's easier for
men than for women to deal with

01:06:09.270 --> 01:06:10.320 align:middle line:10%
some of these things?

01:06:10.320 --> 01:06:11.120 align:middle line:10%
>> Yep.

01:06:11.120 --> 01:06:12.182 align:middle line:10%
>> You think so, eh?

01:06:12.182 --> 01:06:13.980 align:middle line:10%
>> Mm-hmm.

01:06:13.980 --> 01:06:16.410 align:middle line:10%
>> Maybe women need
to pee more often.

01:06:16.410 --> 01:06:18.660 align:middle line:10%
>> The women's community,
I found to be very strong,

01:06:18.660 --> 01:06:22.840 align:middle line:10%
which is, I think, pretty
different compared to many Gulf

01:06:22.840 --> 01:06:23.640 align:middle line:10%
Islands.

01:06:23.640 --> 01:06:26.400 align:middle line:10%
The ones I'm familiar with
are Saturna and Galiano.

01:06:26.400 --> 01:06:28.890 align:middle line:84%
And certainly, there
are strong women there.

01:06:28.890 --> 01:06:33.840 align:middle line:84%
But I found a lot of
patriarchy, like overts--

01:06:33.840 --> 01:06:36.790 align:middle line:84%
really in-your-face
patriarchy there as well.

01:06:36.790 --> 01:06:41.800 align:middle line:84%
So this place has that as well,
but not to the same degree,

01:06:41.800 --> 01:06:42.600 align:middle line:90%
I think.

01:06:42.600 --> 01:06:49.112 align:middle line:84%
And the women are very
much more prominent,

01:06:49.112 --> 01:06:50.570 align:middle line:84%
I guess, in the
community, I think.

01:06:50.570 --> 01:07:13.660 align:middle line:90%


01:07:13.660 --> 01:07:16.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Our youngest daughter was
going into grade 9 when we

01:07:16.920 --> 01:07:17.720 align:middle line:90%
moved out.

01:07:17.720 --> 01:07:19.820 align:middle line:84%
And she had a bit of
a challenge because we

01:07:19.820 --> 01:07:24.380 align:middle line:84%
were leaving a place that
was ideal for a teenager.

01:07:24.380 --> 01:07:26.390 align:middle line:84%
It didn't take her
very long to adapt.

01:07:26.390 --> 01:07:31.010 align:middle line:84%
And she soon felt proud
to bring her friends out

01:07:31.010 --> 01:07:34.160 align:middle line:84%
here and show them what
we did that was different.

01:07:34.160 --> 01:07:37.250 align:middle line:84%
It took her a bit
longer to figure out

01:07:37.250 --> 01:07:39.500 align:middle line:84%
that you couldn't change
your jeans every day

01:07:39.500 --> 01:07:41.600 align:middle line:90%
and stuff like that.

01:07:41.600 --> 01:07:44.950 align:middle line:10%
>> A lot of people who do
this still want to live like

01:07:44.950 --> 01:07:52.590 align:middle line:10%
they're in the city or in the
country with big power supply.

01:07:52.590 --> 01:07:55.220 align:middle line:10%
So they want to live
off-grid, but they

01:07:55.220 --> 01:07:58.260 align:middle line:10%
don't want anything to change
in terms of their lifestyle.

01:07:58.260 --> 01:08:02.000 align:middle line:10%
So that's what's
different about us

01:08:02.000 --> 01:08:04.040 align:middle line:10%
without taking
ourselves too seriously.

01:08:04.040 --> 01:08:10.080 align:middle line:90%


01:08:10.080 --> 01:08:11.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Here, we live
in North America.

01:08:11.720 --> 01:08:17.200 align:middle line:84%
And you just walk into a home
that's been built for us.

01:08:17.200 --> 01:08:23.069 align:middle line:84%
We really wanted to experience
what it was like to actually

01:08:23.069 --> 01:08:25.178 align:middle line:90%
do it all yourself.

01:08:25.178 --> 01:08:26.970 align:middle line:10%
And I'd always had a
dream as a little girl

01:08:26.970 --> 01:08:31.800 align:middle line:10%
to live on "Old
MacDonald Had a Farm."

01:08:31.800 --> 01:08:35.330 align:middle line:10%
That was my dream.

01:08:35.330 --> 01:08:38.560 align:middle line:84%
I wanted very, very much
to work with the horses.

01:08:38.560 --> 01:08:40.840 align:middle line:84%
And part of that was
logging with them.

01:08:40.840 --> 01:08:47.800 align:middle line:84%
We bought two horses that were
made to pull logs out of woods.

01:08:47.800 --> 01:08:52.990 align:middle line:84%
Neither one of us had any
experience in building,

01:08:52.990 --> 01:08:55.350 align:middle line:90%
in logging with horses.

01:08:55.350 --> 01:09:00.670 align:middle line:84%
I'd ridden all my life, but
I've never been behind a horse

01:09:00.670 --> 01:09:02.590 align:middle line:90%
and driven a horse with a cart.

01:09:02.590 --> 01:09:04.330 align:middle line:90%
We have 150 acres.

01:09:04.330 --> 01:09:06.850 align:middle line:84%
So the idea was,
A, we would never

01:09:06.850 --> 01:09:10.260 align:middle line:84%
have to cut down a live tree
because there was enough dead

01:09:10.260 --> 01:09:11.560 align:middle line:90%
fall out there.

01:09:11.560 --> 01:09:12.670 align:middle line:90%
And that's what we did.

01:09:12.670 --> 01:09:17.439 align:middle line:84%
We did that for the first
three or four years.

01:09:17.439 --> 01:09:21.819 align:middle line:84%
The biggest issue that we
are dealing with right now,

01:09:21.819 --> 01:09:28.420 align:middle line:84%
because we couldn't financially
keep it going as an ecotourism

01:09:28.420 --> 01:09:34.310 align:middle line:84%
establishment, we are now left
with the burden of the fallout.

01:09:34.310 --> 01:09:36.740 align:middle line:84%
>> We just didn't have the
numbers of people that you

01:09:36.740 --> 01:09:41.720 align:middle line:84%
needed during the tourist season
to be able to maintain that

01:09:41.720 --> 01:09:43.010 align:middle line:90%
type of lifestyle.

01:09:43.010 --> 01:09:44.899 align:middle line:84%
>> Because it's only
two months of the year.

01:09:44.899 --> 01:09:46.609 align:middle line:90%
You've got July and August.

01:09:46.609 --> 01:09:48.260 align:middle line:90%
And you can't make the money.

01:09:48.260 --> 01:09:49.500 align:middle line:90%
You just can't do it.

01:09:49.500 --> 01:09:52.760 align:middle line:84%
So either you have to have
money to live off-the-grid,

01:09:52.760 --> 01:09:57.980 align:middle line:84%
to own outright your property
and have no mortgage.

01:09:57.980 --> 01:10:00.800 align:middle line:90%
So we couldn't do it.

01:10:00.800 --> 01:10:02.285 align:middle line:90%
We just couldn't do it.

01:10:02.285 --> 01:10:07.240 align:middle line:90%


01:10:07.240 --> 01:10:09.710 align:middle line:84%
>> So enter working
off the farm.

01:10:09.710 --> 01:10:12.110 align:middle line:84%
Judy's working off
the farm as a cook.

01:10:12.110 --> 01:10:14.500 align:middle line:84%
I'm working off the farm
right now as a security

01:10:14.500 --> 01:10:16.150 align:middle line:90%
guard at a hospital.

01:10:16.150 --> 01:10:18.830 align:middle line:84%
That changes the whole
off-grid situation.

01:10:18.830 --> 01:10:22.690 align:middle line:84%
>> We were functioning
with the weather before.

01:10:22.690 --> 01:10:24.620 align:middle line:84%
You can't function
like that now.

01:10:24.620 --> 01:10:25.420 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

01:10:25.420 --> 01:10:28.070 align:middle line:84%
Now we come home
and we want things.

01:10:28.070 --> 01:10:30.400 align:middle line:84%
And I've got four
hours, then I have

01:10:30.400 --> 01:10:32.920 align:middle line:90%
to either sleep or go to work.

01:10:32.920 --> 01:10:34.360 align:middle line:90%
So we use more power.

01:10:34.360 --> 01:10:39.120 align:middle line:84%
Now it becomes a
major pain in the ass.

01:10:39.120 --> 01:10:41.850 align:middle line:84%
>> In one sense, you
have to weigh the ethical

01:10:41.850 --> 01:10:45.630 align:middle line:84%
or the ideological
side to the practical.

01:10:45.630 --> 01:10:47.220 align:middle line:84%
Our other option,
and this is very

01:10:47.220 --> 01:10:52.240 align:middle line:84%
ironic, is that Jim go out
west to work as a driver for--

01:10:52.240 --> 01:10:53.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Oil sands.

01:10:53.040 --> 01:10:55.480 align:middle line:90%
>> --oil sands.

01:10:55.480 --> 01:10:58.450 align:middle line:84%
>> The big part of what's
next is we will be on-grid.

01:10:58.450 --> 01:11:02.050 align:middle line:84%
>> If Jim were able to go out
west, first thing we would do--

01:11:02.050 --> 01:11:09.250 align:middle line:84%
would probably take us $20,000
to get the lines in and then

01:11:09.250 --> 01:11:13.090 align:middle line:84%
get a system going whereby I
can have running hot water and I

01:11:13.090 --> 01:11:16.930 align:middle line:84%
can have a little propane
stove with an oven here.

01:11:16.930 --> 01:11:23.460 align:middle line:10%
I have to have some
easier option here.

01:11:23.460 --> 01:11:27.690 align:middle line:84%
The people I work with just
cannot possibly understand how

01:11:27.690 --> 01:11:29.190 align:middle line:90%
I've survived this long.

01:11:29.190 --> 01:11:32.680 align:middle line:84%
They have spent the last 50
years getting away from this.

01:11:32.680 --> 01:11:36.430 align:middle line:84%
So they don't want
to go back to this.

01:11:36.430 --> 01:11:38.760 align:middle line:84%
Whether you live
off-the-grid or on-the-grid,

01:11:38.760 --> 01:11:40.440 align:middle line:90%
you still deal with life.

01:11:40.440 --> 01:11:45.780 align:middle line:84%
And life can be very,
very roller coastery.

01:11:45.780 --> 01:11:47.520 align:middle line:90%
We love it here.

01:11:47.520 --> 01:11:49.610 align:middle line:90%
I mean, who wouldn't?

01:11:49.610 --> 01:11:51.060 align:middle line:90%
This is paradise.

01:11:51.060 --> 01:11:53.280 align:middle line:90%
It's a little piece of heaven.

01:11:53.280 --> 01:11:56.130 align:middle line:84%
We have no issues
with neighbors.

01:11:56.130 --> 01:11:59.790 align:middle line:84%
We have 150 acres
surrounding us.

01:11:59.790 --> 01:12:02.190 align:middle line:84%
I can have my horses
in my backyard.

01:12:02.190 --> 01:12:05.280 align:middle line:90%
I can look out my window.

01:12:05.280 --> 01:12:08.970 align:middle line:84%
It's the most complicated
life I've ever lived.

01:12:08.970 --> 01:12:10.890 align:middle line:90%
And that's the truth.

01:12:10.890 --> 01:12:16.320 align:middle line:84%
I have never felt more
stressed than I feel today.

01:12:16.320 --> 01:12:24.610 align:middle line:90%


01:12:24.610 --> 01:12:28.960 align:middle line:10%
>> The thing about it is
everybody comes here with

01:12:28.960 --> 01:12:31.000 align:middle line:10%
a dream.

01:12:31.000 --> 01:12:34.480 align:middle line:10%
And after about
four to six months,

01:12:34.480 --> 01:12:37.980 align:middle line:10%
they find out that
the dream doesn't fit.

01:12:37.980 --> 01:12:40.840 align:middle line:84%
And the smart ones
change the dream,

01:12:40.840 --> 01:12:43.060 align:middle line:84%
and they're the
ones that stay here.

01:12:43.060 --> 01:12:47.350 align:middle line:84%
The ones that try to make
this place fit their dream

01:12:47.350 --> 01:12:50.590 align:middle line:90%
usually don't stick around.

01:12:50.590 --> 01:12:54.550 align:middle line:84%
The learning curve for
somebody moving out of the city

01:12:54.550 --> 01:12:57.550 align:middle line:84%
coming to this place
is straight up.

01:12:57.550 --> 01:12:58.930 align:middle line:90%
Straight up.

01:12:58.930 --> 01:13:01.300 align:middle line:84%
You've got to
understand plumbing.

01:13:01.300 --> 01:13:05.650 align:middle line:84%
You've got to
understand basic wiring.

01:13:05.650 --> 01:13:08.710 align:middle line:84%
Every coffee table
in the suburbs

01:13:08.710 --> 01:13:14.230 align:middle line:84%
has got country life on
it with glossy photographs

01:13:14.230 --> 01:13:18.340 align:middle line:84%
of all these gorgeous
houses full of antiques

01:13:18.340 --> 01:13:19.900 align:middle line:90%
and knickknacks.

01:13:19.900 --> 01:13:21.507 align:middle line:84%
And they have this
notion that that's

01:13:21.507 --> 01:13:22.840 align:middle line:90%
the way you live in the country.

01:13:22.840 --> 01:13:25.810 align:middle line:90%
Well, you bloody well don't.

01:13:25.810 --> 01:13:27.870 align:middle line:84%
Nobody's got the time
to dust that shit.

01:13:27.870 --> 01:13:36.470 align:middle line:90%


01:13:36.470 --> 01:13:38.490 align:middle line:84%
>> My grandfather and
I were very close.

01:13:38.490 --> 01:13:42.530 align:middle line:84%
So I'm the one he told
all his stories to.

01:13:42.530 --> 01:13:44.600 align:middle line:84%
He left me the
island with a promise

01:13:44.600 --> 01:13:47.930 align:middle line:84%
to do my best to keep it in
the family or protect it.

01:13:47.930 --> 01:13:51.310 align:middle line:84%
And that's the promise
that I've kept.

01:13:51.310 --> 01:13:54.090 align:middle line:84%
When I used to stay out
here with my grandparents

01:13:54.090 --> 01:13:58.700 align:middle line:84%
in the '50s, '60s, they had
a very small grid system.

01:13:58.700 --> 01:14:02.810 align:middle line:84%
So every house, I don't know if
it was 60 amps, 80 amps tops--

01:14:02.810 --> 01:14:04.520 align:middle line:90%
very small electrical services.

01:14:04.520 --> 01:14:07.200 align:middle line:10%
So when the neighbor down the
street turned on their toaster,

01:14:07.200 --> 01:14:09.100 align:middle line:10%
your TV went like this.

01:14:09.100 --> 01:14:13.140 align:middle line:10%
You understood there was
a limited amount of power.

01:14:13.140 --> 01:14:16.680 align:middle line:10%
And now there's no demand
metering on residents.

01:14:16.680 --> 01:14:18.650 align:middle line:90%
There's no feedback loop.

01:14:18.650 --> 01:14:20.450 align:middle line:84%
You can use any amount
of power you want.

01:14:20.450 --> 01:14:22.880 align:middle line:10%
You can run all your
electric heaters at once.

01:14:22.880 --> 01:14:25.200 align:middle line:10%
You're going to get a bill.

01:14:25.200 --> 01:14:26.750 align:middle line:10%
Price is a great factor.

01:14:26.750 --> 01:14:29.420 align:middle line:10%
But in a way, it
means that if price

01:14:29.420 --> 01:14:32.180 align:middle line:10%
is the only control
of consumption,

01:14:32.180 --> 01:14:34.890 align:middle line:10%
it just means that wealthy
people can use a whole bunch

01:14:34.890 --> 01:14:36.020 align:middle line:10%
because they can afford to.

01:14:36.020 --> 01:14:39.560 align:middle line:84%
So what I find interesting
with human behavior

01:14:39.560 --> 01:14:44.960 align:middle line:84%
is that if people can access
the power, they'll use it.

01:14:44.960 --> 01:14:47.450 align:middle line:84%
If they can't, they'll
take it to the limit

01:14:47.450 --> 01:14:50.040 align:middle line:84%
and then go, oh,
that's the limit.

01:14:50.040 --> 01:14:51.500 align:middle line:10%
>> If you bring
a paradigm where,

01:14:51.500 --> 01:14:54.330 align:middle line:10%
I want to convert my city
house to being off-the-grid,

01:14:54.330 --> 01:14:56.900 align:middle line:10%
and I want my dishwasher and
my dryer and my washing machine

01:14:56.900 --> 01:14:58.040 align:middle line:10%
and blah, blah, blah.

01:14:58.040 --> 01:15:00.200 align:middle line:10%
Well, that's all
fine if you've got

01:15:00.200 --> 01:15:03.170 align:middle line:10%
$45,000 to spend
on a power system

01:15:03.170 --> 01:15:05.990 align:middle line:10%
to run your house renewably.

01:15:05.990 --> 01:15:10.360 align:middle line:84%
All that you've proven is
that a person with $45,000

01:15:10.360 --> 01:15:13.430 align:middle line:84%
can live off-the-grid just
like we live on-the-grid.

01:15:13.430 --> 01:15:17.030 align:middle line:84%
That is not really
progress in my mind.

01:15:17.030 --> 01:15:24.830 align:middle line:10%
>> Do we want people in the city
to be independent with respect

01:15:24.830 --> 01:15:27.620 align:middle line:10%
in electrical generation?

01:15:27.620 --> 01:15:33.880 align:middle line:10%
Or do we want them to take
ownership and understanding?

01:15:33.880 --> 01:15:36.380 align:middle line:84%
>> The first thing I would say
to someone who wanted to live

01:15:36.380 --> 01:15:41.180 align:middle line:84%
off-the-grid is first turn
everything off and live without

01:15:41.180 --> 01:15:45.560 align:middle line:84%
electricity for as
long as you dare.

01:15:45.560 --> 01:15:48.230 align:middle line:84%
And then you will
have a starting place

01:15:48.230 --> 01:15:53.870 align:middle line:84%
from which to truly appreciate
what it is to be off-grid.

01:15:53.870 --> 01:15:57.690 align:middle line:84%
And then from there, you
could start by, for example,

01:15:57.690 --> 01:16:01.460 align:middle line:84%
buying a small solar panel and
a car battery or something.

01:16:01.460 --> 01:16:03.590 align:middle line:84%
And you could say,
now I'm going to live

01:16:03.590 --> 01:16:07.220 align:middle line:90%
on what I can make with this.

01:16:07.220 --> 01:16:10.760 align:middle line:10%
>> I think there's something
deeply rooted in what it means

01:16:10.760 --> 01:16:16.430 align:middle line:10%
to be human, to have the
connection between being

01:16:16.430 --> 01:16:19.970 align:middle line:10%
productive and having stuff.

01:16:19.970 --> 01:16:23.150 align:middle line:10%
In our society, that
connection has become tenuous.

01:16:23.150 --> 01:16:25.250 align:middle line:84%
You get a paycheck,
but it's very hard

01:16:25.250 --> 01:16:28.160 align:middle line:84%
to see what you're doing
in your office actually

01:16:28.160 --> 01:16:30.110 align:middle line:90%
connects to producing anything.

01:16:30.110 --> 01:16:33.290 align:middle line:84%
For me, to be in a
physical environment

01:16:33.290 --> 01:16:36.680 align:middle line:84%
where taking care of
stuff, making sure

01:16:36.680 --> 01:16:38.960 align:middle line:84%
that I have wood for
the winter, making sure

01:16:38.960 --> 01:16:41.990 align:middle line:84%
that the various systems
are working properly, that I

01:16:41.990 --> 01:16:43.130 align:middle line:90%
have to take care of them.

01:16:43.130 --> 01:16:47.090 align:middle line:84%
And as I invest in those things,
then my needs are satisfied.

01:16:47.090 --> 01:16:51.320 align:middle line:84%
Seeing that connection,
I think, is--

01:16:51.320 --> 01:16:54.070 align:middle line:84%
there's something deeply
healthy about that.

01:16:54.070 --> 01:16:56.600 align:middle line:90%


01:16:56.600 --> 01:16:57.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Is it doable?

01:16:57.750 --> 01:16:58.550 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

01:16:58.550 --> 01:16:59.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Of course it is.

01:16:59.900 --> 01:17:02.930 align:middle line:84%
We can do anything that
we set our minds to.

01:17:02.930 --> 01:17:03.860 align:middle line:10%
Anything.

01:17:03.860 --> 01:17:06.260 align:middle line:10%
I built my house.

01:17:06.260 --> 01:17:08.400 align:middle line:10%
I live off-grid.

01:17:08.400 --> 01:17:10.520 align:middle line:90%
Some people do amazing things.

01:17:10.520 --> 01:17:13.190 align:middle line:84%
Lots of people do
amazing things.

01:17:13.190 --> 01:17:16.220 align:middle line:84%
But are there enough
people who think it's

01:17:16.220 --> 01:17:19.330 align:middle line:90%
worth it to save the planet?

01:17:19.330 --> 01:17:20.900 align:middle line:90%
I'm not so sure.

01:17:20.900 --> 01:17:25.220 align:middle line:84%
As soon as you step outside
of this little closed group,

01:17:25.220 --> 01:17:28.400 align:middle line:84%
you notice that there
is an ocean of people

01:17:28.400 --> 01:17:32.150 align:middle line:84%
who have no clue and
who are not interested.

01:17:32.150 --> 01:17:36.260 align:middle line:84%
On my bad days, I think
humans are a parasite

01:17:36.260 --> 01:17:39.620 align:middle line:84%
and the earth will get
rid of us sooner or later.

01:17:39.620 --> 01:17:41.480 align:middle line:90%
And it doesn't bother me at all.

01:17:41.480 --> 01:17:44.910 align:middle line:84%
>> It's being fanned fast
and furious by the television

01:17:44.910 --> 01:17:47.290 align:middle line:84%
because that's what
they want you to do.

01:17:47.290 --> 01:17:49.340 align:middle line:84%
They want you to
consume and work.

01:17:49.340 --> 01:17:52.400 align:middle line:84%
Because the mandate of our
civilization is to destroy

01:17:52.400 --> 01:17:55.760 align:middle line:90%
the planet as quick as possible.

01:17:55.760 --> 01:17:58.360 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it sounds silly, but
that explains everything.

01:17:58.360 --> 01:18:00.070 align:middle line:10%
And that's where
it all comes from.

01:18:00.070 --> 01:18:04.560 align:middle line:10%
The drive to just have
it all now regardless

01:18:04.560 --> 01:18:05.600 align:middle line:10%
of the consequences.

01:18:05.600 --> 01:18:08.715 align:middle line:84%
And that's the kind of system
that we're operating under.

01:18:08.715 --> 01:18:10.090 align:middle line:84%
It's the collective
consciousness

01:18:10.090 --> 01:18:11.270 align:middle line:90%
in the civilization.

01:18:11.270 --> 01:18:15.680 align:middle line:10%
People as a-- humanity
as a conglomerate entity

01:18:15.680 --> 01:18:18.665 align:middle line:10%
is like on this trip where we're
going to just trash everything

01:18:18.665 --> 01:18:19.790 align:middle line:10%
until there's nothing left.

01:18:19.790 --> 01:18:21.560 align:middle line:84%
And there's nobody
that can stop it.

01:18:21.560 --> 01:18:23.090 align:middle line:90%
It'll have to stop itself.

01:18:23.090 --> 01:18:24.850 align:middle line:90%
And it will.

01:18:24.850 --> 01:18:26.447 align:middle line:90%
Things will change.

01:18:26.447 --> 01:18:28.530 align:middle line:84%
It's not going to be pretty,
but they will change.

01:18:28.530 --> 01:18:33.730 align:middle line:90%


01:18:33.730 --> 01:18:37.250 align:middle line:84%
>> That's what's got
lost in a lot of this.

01:18:37.250 --> 01:18:42.850 align:middle line:10%
And I worry that those that have
lost all the skills of taking

01:18:42.850 --> 01:18:46.990 align:middle line:10%
care of themselves and
having to actually work

01:18:46.990 --> 01:18:50.320 align:middle line:10%
in harmony with nature
in order to survive,

01:18:50.320 --> 01:18:54.370 align:middle line:10%
that there's going to
be such a mass of people

01:18:54.370 --> 01:18:57.490 align:middle line:10%
that don't get it at all.

01:18:57.490 --> 01:19:00.180 align:middle line:10%
>> I had 20 years in
federal government.

01:19:00.180 --> 01:19:02.500 align:middle line:10%
And after a while,
you just sort of come

01:19:02.500 --> 01:19:06.040 align:middle line:10%
to understand that all of
this process that we have

01:19:06.040 --> 01:19:08.200 align:middle line:10%
in our society that's
supposed to make

01:19:08.200 --> 01:19:11.780 align:middle line:10%
this a better place
for environment

01:19:11.780 --> 01:19:14.250 align:middle line:10%
is not really working.

01:19:14.250 --> 01:19:16.422 align:middle line:84%
And that you are
inside of a system.

01:19:16.422 --> 01:19:18.130 align:middle line:84%
And you're in there
initially because you

01:19:18.130 --> 01:19:20.200 align:middle line:90%
think you can change it.

01:19:20.200 --> 01:19:24.760 align:middle line:10%
>> It was the corporate world
that really opened my eyes

01:19:24.760 --> 01:19:29.470 align:middle line:10%
to just how little
the corporations care.

01:19:29.470 --> 01:19:31.090 align:middle line:90%
For example, our food.

01:19:31.090 --> 01:19:33.340 align:middle line:84%
We don't know where
our food comes from.

01:19:33.340 --> 01:19:37.180 align:middle line:84%
And the only time that the
corporations will do anything

01:19:37.180 --> 01:19:40.430 align:middle line:84%
in a green sense is if
the people push for it.

01:19:40.430 --> 01:19:44.170 align:middle line:10%
>> We need to stop buying
energy from utilities,

01:19:44.170 --> 01:19:48.520 align:middle line:10%
from fuel companies, from coal
companies at such ridiculously,

01:19:48.520 --> 01:19:50.950 align:middle line:10%
heavily subsidized rates.

01:19:50.950 --> 01:19:53.200 align:middle line:84%
If there were real prices
for the energy we use,

01:19:53.200 --> 01:19:56.080 align:middle line:84%
renewable energy would
be a screaming bargain

01:19:56.080 --> 01:20:00.010 align:middle line:84%
and people would be banging
down the doors to buy it.

01:20:00.010 --> 01:20:03.250 align:middle line:90%
However, as long as--

01:20:03.250 --> 01:20:06.880 align:middle line:84%
it's cheap to take a mountain
top off some poor chunk

01:20:06.880 --> 01:20:10.810 align:middle line:84%
of Virginia or Pennsylvania
or North Carolina

01:20:10.810 --> 01:20:17.140 align:middle line:84%
and profitable and subsidized
by a variety of business

01:20:17.140 --> 01:20:18.700 align:middle line:90%
interests.

01:20:18.700 --> 01:20:21.530 align:middle line:90%
We'll hear about clean coal.

01:20:21.530 --> 01:20:28.090 align:middle line:84%
We'll see wonderful ads about
what a great idea fracking is--

01:20:28.090 --> 01:20:33.070 align:middle line:84%
until we start paying for
poisoning people's wells.

01:20:33.070 --> 01:20:36.580 align:middle line:84%
And if we start paying
those real costs,

01:20:36.580 --> 01:20:40.680 align:middle line:84%
we'll see a real change in
perception and usage of energy.

01:20:40.680 --> 01:20:46.000 align:middle line:90%


01:20:46.000 --> 01:20:50.890 align:middle line:84%
>> We've taken that wonderful
concept of North America

01:20:50.890 --> 01:20:58.110 align:middle line:84%
pioneering and entrepreneurial
spirit and we adopted it

01:20:58.110 --> 01:21:03.300 align:middle line:84%
to our hearts as
back to the earthers.

01:21:03.300 --> 01:21:09.010 align:middle line:84%
And it didn't occur
to us, that, perhaps,

01:21:09.010 --> 01:21:11.550 align:middle line:90%
was colossally selfish.

01:21:11.550 --> 01:21:16.987 align:middle line:84%
There's really no
reason four families

01:21:16.987 --> 01:21:18.195 align:middle line:90%
couldn't share this property.

01:21:18.195 --> 01:21:20.700 align:middle line:90%


01:21:20.700 --> 01:21:23.670 align:middle line:84%
And in most parts of
the world, they would.

01:21:23.670 --> 01:21:29.160 align:middle line:84%
We live in a place where we
have the ability and the soil

01:21:29.160 --> 01:21:34.580 align:middle line:84%
and water resources to grow
the majority of our food.

01:21:34.580 --> 01:21:40.390 align:middle line:84%
Our heat energy comes from
trees that grow on our property.

01:21:40.390 --> 01:21:42.195 align:middle line:84%
Our electricity
falls out of the sky.

01:21:42.195 --> 01:21:45.040 align:middle line:90%


01:21:45.040 --> 01:21:51.960 align:middle line:84%
We have the luxury of being
largely independent from what's

01:21:51.960 --> 01:21:56.340 align:middle line:84%
going on economically or
socially in the world.

01:21:56.340 --> 01:21:59.290 align:middle line:90%


01:21:59.290 --> 01:22:07.960 align:middle line:84%
This, in true North American
terms, is a colossal luxury.

01:22:07.960 --> 01:22:09.070 align:middle line:90%
What's wrong with that?

01:22:09.070 --> 01:22:12.240 align:middle line:90%


01:22:12.240 --> 01:22:15.830 align:middle line:84%
We can't afford to have
three billion people being

01:22:15.830 --> 01:22:16.670 align:middle line:90%
